An example for plotting window densities using MACE package

**INSTALATION**

conda create -n mace
conda activate mace
mamba install -c mahajrod mace

**INPUT**
To draw the densities of heterozygosity you will need a VCF file with heterozygous SNPs only.You also will need four more files (all must have no headers):

1. whitelist - a file with ids of scaffolds you wish to see on the plot (one id per line)

2. syn file - a file with synonyms for scaffolds ids, which will be shown on the plot. It is a two column tab separated file. Which column to use as a key, andwhich as a syn is controlled by script options

3. orderlist - file with order of scaffolds on the plot (one id per line). If a syn file was set it must contain synonyms instead of original ids.

4. len file - file with length of scaffolds. Two column tab-separated file. First column should contain original scaffold ids, second - length of the corresponding scaffolds

**RUNNING**

Simply ./CMDS.bash or check this file if you wish to adjust options.

This script will draw densities of SNPs from the example vcf, which contains obly filtered and heterozygous positions.
Window size is set to 1000000 (1 Mbp), window step to 100000 (100 kbp), respectively.
Windows are divided to categories according to the following thresholds 0, 0.1, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0, 1.25, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5 SNPs/kbp.

